{
  "stem": "10181.5",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I guess I must have looked like a scarecrow, you know, because I was wearing clothes which-- which probably was-- even if I hadn't grown much, it was too small for me and was rotting and full of lice.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And-- and-- and you get these-- you know, these scabs on [INAUDIBLE] over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They didn't-- they didn't even want to open the door, and when they opened the door, they said, well, we are refugees ourself.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We don't have any food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then I sat down on-- on sort of on the front stoop of somebody's house.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And and some-- some American soldiers came, OK, down the street.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I think the second or third one stopped to ask me who I was.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I didn't understand what he was saying because I didn't know English.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So strangely enough, he spoke in-- in-- in sort of Yiddish, you know.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was-- he probably was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, because I understood German, and it wasn't-- wasn't clean German what he spoke.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- it was like Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I told him, you know, what-- that I was-- there was a train nearby, and I-- and my sister was there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'd been looking for food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he started to dig out his rations and gave them to me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then he stopped a jeep and, you know, put me on the jeep to take me back to where the train was.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then other soldiers came and-- and gave their food, you know, in order to bring it to-- to the people in-- in at the train.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And of course, then the Germans saw through their windows what was happening.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then they came out and-- and bought bread or whatever.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "All of a sudden they had food.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, they wanted to look good for-- to the American soldiers, I guess.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So they took us back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Some of the soldiers took us back by jeep.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And-- they sat off next to me like this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I'm sure they didn't want to touch me, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But I've never seen anything like it before, you see.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I laugh now-- it wasn't really funny-- because we were really-- must have seemed like something from a different world, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they had not been prepared.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I mean, if anybody tells you the Americans came to liberate, they didn't come to liberate.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They came to fight the war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They didn't come to liberate anybody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They came to liberate-- it-- it was by coincidence.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They happened upon a train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They happened upon a camp, so they liberated the camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But they were not ready for the kind of conditions because these are the kind of conditions which don't exist, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "These are subhuman conditions, you know, where you have people dying, you know, on the-- on-- on in cattle-- people in cattle wagons dying.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And so they came upon the train and didn't know quite what to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "You know, I mean, everybody knew we were liberated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Everybody cheered.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But that was it, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Then we had to sort of find our own way to find food, you know, from the local German population.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The Americans who were in the area did give their rations, whatever they had with them, they gave us, you know.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But for that day, nothing much else happened till the next day or the day or-- the day after, when--",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was in-- I would say around April 15, you  know, give or take.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- [INAUDIBLE] a week after we left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like I said, one of the German soldiers afterwards said that Roosevelt had died.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, you know, if you figure we probably didn't know this right away, and-- and-- so I think it was around April 15, OK?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, right, right.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- my birthday's on April 21, yeah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Didn't-- I didn't really bother me very much, my birthday, at the time, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Didn't think about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then, the next day or the day after, I think it was the-- it must have been the medical officer of the unit, you know, came, and he looked.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I guess he was in shock, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then he decided right away that he has to evacuate the train, get everybody off that train first of all.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If you want to take care of them, can't leave them on the train, you know, packed like sardines and-- and-- and-- no proper sanitation, and-- and-- and no nothing, you know.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they started to take us to this little town where there was some buildings where-- with apartments which had been abandoned by German officers who had fled because of the advance of the American army.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They put it in there together with another family, OK, another Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
